condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Project Agreement Section I.A.1 - Project Management Unit | Description :CDR shall establish, not later than one(1) month after the Effective Date, and thereafter maintain the Project Management Unit throughout the life of the project withstaffing, resources and terms of reference satisfactory to the Bank. | Due Date :30-Oct-2015

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Section D.1 - ESMP and RAP Implementation | Description :CDR shall ensure that the Project iscarried out in accordance with the ESMP and the RAP and shall not amend, suspend, abrogate, repeal or waive any provision of theESMP and the RAP without prior approval of the Bank | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Section D.2 - Land expropriation and resettlement | Description :CDR shall ensure that, priorto commencing any civil works under the Project, all resettlement measures set forth in the RAP in relation to the specific civilwork, shall have been fully executed, including the full payment for Land Acquisition and Resettlement Compensations prior todisplacement and/or the provision of relocation assistance to all Displaced Persons | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Section D.6 - Construction Supervision and Quality Assurance | Description :CDR shallimplement the Construction Supervision and Quality Assurance Plan; Emergency Preparedness Plan; Instrumentation Plan; andOperation and Maintenance Plan (collectively “Dam Safety Plans”) in a timely manner satisfactory to the Bank; not amend, revise orwaive any of the Dam Safety Plans without the prior written agreement of the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Section D.6(a) - Dam Safety Panel | Description :CDR shall maintain an independent Dam SafetyPanel of Experts (DSPE) comprising at least four (4) experts acceptable to the Bank, under terms of reference acceptable to theBank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
